<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoTitle>Recruiting</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]> <![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>Prophecy
was built on a group of people that enjoy each other's friendship. In keeping
with that spirit of unity and friendship we have put together this new policy
to ensure new candidates for membership meet our strict guidelines. Not
everyone whom is sponsored at any given time will be considered for membership.
If this is the case, an explaination will be posted for all current members to
view.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><br>
Roles of the Candidate - Get sponsored. You will need 2 Sponsors from the
current Members. Group with a total of 6 Prophecy officers on no less than 6
occasions. You have a maximum time frame of 30 days to meet the requirements
and satisfy the officers as to your ability and attitude and worth, before a
vote will be drawn. If in this 30 day time, you fail to group with the officers
in open events or events that are schedules by Prophecy, you will be dropped
form the recruiting process. Thirty days is a fair amount of time to get in
groups and make contacts, as there are events of one kind or another almost
nightly. It is "Your" responsibility as a recruit, to contact
officers regarding events you may join. *Read our charter and rules, as well as
the recruiting process in it's entirety before the process begins.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]> <![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>Roles
of the Sponsor - Sponsor will post in the recruiting forum the name of the
candidate that is being sponsored, as well as sending an email to the Officers
listed at the bottom of this Policy, with this information. Sponsor will give
the candidate a list of Prophecy Officers, as well as the url for Guildworld,
so they may read our charter, rules, and recruiting process in it's entirety.
Once the recruit has grouped with a total of 6 officers on no less than 6
occasions, and has found to be sound in ability, attitude and can provide worth
to the guild as a whole, a vote will be drawn in the Officers forum, and the
results posted accordingly. If a sponsor cannot follow these steps for his/her
recruit, there is no need to post for sponsorship. It is NOT the officers’
responsibility to get your recruit into groups. The Officers will make an
attempt on occasion to do so, but remember, it is the responsibility of the
recruit to make contacts with the Officers about events. It would be most
helpful if "inguild people" would inform their recruits of possible
time and dates, but it is not a requirement you do so. The list of current
Officers is at the bottom of this Policy as well as the 4 email address you
will need.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]> <![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>Roles
of Prophecy Members - Prophecy members need to check the recruiting forum and
be aware of the list, so they too can keep an eye out for shouts or other
information regarding candidates, and go out of their way to group with
potential candidates. If you as a member have problems with a recruit, it is
"YOUR" responsibility to email your concerns to Officers. /tells in
game are *not considered to be sufficient for this. Your problem(s) or
concern(s) will be posted to the Officers forum in it's text entirety
*excluding name and email address.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><br>
Officers - After receiving email from the sponsors, and reviewing the postings
on the recruiting forum, the Officers will then discuss the candidate(s) and
decide if there are negatives with him/her in the Officers forum before
continuing the process. If there are any negative comments those will be discussed.
Officers will then make a decision, based on feedback, whether the candidate is
in or out for the recruiting process. After votes have been cast, results will
be posted in public as to the results of the vote taken 
	<p>

